        "subject": "LU-19859 scripts: fix bash path for developer scripts",
        "message": "LU-19859 scripts: fix bash path for developer scripts\n\nHard-coding /usr/bin/bash prevents editing files on MacOS with\nthe Git commit hooks enabled, since MacOS still uses /bin/bash.\nChange them over to \"/usr/bin/env bash\" so they run everywhere.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nFixes: 45418aa71a (\"LU-19859 scripts: Use actual bash binary\")\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: I364af44d277a4746eae561df8ab837d1313ebbe5\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64447\nReviewed-by: Nathaniel Clark <nclark@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Timothy Day <tday141@gmail.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
